column5: A good weather day -8 for a high today so took off and got to the shack at noon.Drilled 2 holes today but ended up fishing from one.Dropped transducer in and only thing I saw was the bottom.Not many fish moving through but enough here and there as they moved through in smaller schools than normal.Cheated in the beginning with live bait just to get my 4 supper fish.Even found a few stickle backs and the walleyes jumped on them when they came through.Used a few different lures and basically if some fish came through they would eat them. Still had a good bite catching 30 or so in the 3 hours I was there.Cheap day for Clarks using 2 stickler backs.lol.Used the hair jigs again from Bill and they worked very well again as did the vibratos.Had a white out a few times and coukd barely see the shoreline.Good thing its only 100 yrs from shack or I might off got lost.
Thanks, John, enjoy the pictures so much!!! Bill
Can't say much about that walleye,but that's a trophy stickle,one for the wall.
John, shame on you for hurting those poor fish. Please send them to me right away, and I will do my best to revive them. Feel free to only send fillets and dry ice to save on postage.
Funny man.Best I can do is send a pic later of what there going to look like on our plates tonight.
That was one tough stickle back. I really can't beleive people would through them out and not use them.
